section#section_issue
  .container
    h1(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px); opacity:0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px); opacity:1") Issue
    .row.col-md-8.col-sm-12(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px); opacity:0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px); opacity:1")
      img.map(src="https://i.imgur.com/BBpyCTC.jpg", alt="")
    .row
      .issue.issue1.col-sm-4(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px); opacity:0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px); opacity:1") Monotone use of the site
        .text As a residential area, the site located in the center of the city and right next to Banqiao station, where is surrounded by different land uses, such as public authorities, department stores, office buildings, restaurants and so on, with an old and monotone profile.To reach to goal of 10-min city, the access form the site to other uses is dangerous, in the meanwhile, the activities on the site can’t other nearby opportunities for the residents.
        
        
      .issue.issue2.col-sm-4(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px); opacity:0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px); opacity:1") Pedestrian-unfriendly streets
        .text The lack of sidewalks force pedestrians  to jostle with cars and motorcycles for the right to walk, which is dangerous especially for kids, elders and physically challenged.  The ability of accessing different land uses (schools, MRT/train/bus stations, shops …etc.) from the site at the radius of 10-min walking distance shrinks, due to the evasive actions the pedestrians have to take while walking on the streets.
        
        
      .issue.issue3.col-sm-4(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px); opacity:0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px); opacity:1") Lack of public utilities and barrier-free facilities
        .text Postwar walk-up apartments, common to see in New Taipei city, were built in 1940s and 1950s. Nowadays, to live in these buildings, the residents have no space to develop their social lives in the neighbourhood. It is also challenging for the elders and physically challenged to live here, since there’s no elevator to move up. Municipality subsidize inhabitants to install elevators to ameliorate this situation, with little success.
        
        
