section#section_concept
  .container
    h1(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px); opacity:0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px); opacity:1") Concept
    .row
      .description.col-sm-6(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px); opacity:0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px); opacity:1") 1. Improve vertical movement in the postwar walk-up apartment.<br><br>2. Free up the street and parking lots for pedestrians, social activites and emergency situation.<br><br>3. Increase the diversity and flexibitility of land use in the nieghborhood.<br><br><br><br>"TieLine" is a light railway system installed into the roads. It will not only be expanded from the site to the radius of 10-min transporting distance, but the vertical movements will also be attached to the apartments. The electric cart moving on the railway with constant speed   are designed to fit different needs eg. for commuting, firefighting, collecting garbage, distributing parcels, moving upward and downward, . exercising, working and selling stuffs.

      img.concept(src="https://i.imgur.com/SdkgIML.png", alt="").col-sm-6(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px); opacity:0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px); opacity:1")
      
      
      
